laboratory_examinations.findings: Intact mitral leaflets, no evidence of endocarditis or paravalvular abscess. Marked disruption and fistulization of the anterior mitral annulus with a 9 Ã— 7 mm irregularly shaped opening. Systolic left ventricular-to-left atrial flow through the fistula with Doppler signal characteristic of mitral regurgitation. Biventricular cavity size, systolic function, and estimated pulmonary artery systolic pressure were within normal limits.
Normal findings, without evidence of valvular pathology.
